<subSubSection id="0DC7069BFA55EAF49D20F6DA7BE51ACE" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="776CF055687C1D1B582617F825DCFADA" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CEADE4FD40FBA1314AA2C2E31D0FB448" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The species is endemic to the upper elevations of the Sierra San Pedro 
<normalizedToken id="9EC5C4F8632724FB0864A96CB2AE4FCB" originalValue="Mártir">Martir</normalizedToken>
, Baja California but apparently was not collected until 1962. Reported and described as 
<taxonomicName id="FD5676B2C144A6F54B53BD02D2B45277" authorityName="Vasey" authorityYear="1887" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orcuttiana">
<emphasis id="2818A7EED781818CCA1CC11825C275CF" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Poa orcuttiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vasey (= 
<taxonomicName id="430403AD333133623458748B3C27D5FC" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secunda">
<emphasis id="568F89096E57C41006EB36E07259572D" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Poa secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF069502C8DB595E9A658E216AB7F3EE" author="Gould, FW" journalOrPublisher="Australian Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B20" refString="Gould, FW, Moran, R, 1981. The grasses of Baja California, Mexico. San Diego Society of Natural History, Memoir 12:1-140." title="The grasses of Baja California, Mexico. San Diego Society of Natural History, Memoir 12: 1 - 140." year="1981">Gould and Moran (1981)</bibRefCitation>
; the five collections they mentioned are all 
<taxonomicName id="C9B7F3703DA0830E0F2F4B143743C51F" authorityName="Soreng, Madrono 48 (2): 123, f. 1. 2001" authorityYear="2002" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bajaensis">
<emphasis id="79C7D257D8882D080CDD4CA4217A6BC7" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Poa bajaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens were sometimes labeled as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="EAA525406A4F22E542C3CD8F820276C5" authorityName="Rydb" authorityYear="1905" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interior">
<emphasis id="0253B96A477C98673C1BAD9440F6F488" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Poa interior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rydb.&quot; (e.g., at SD and TAES). It is well marked by its sparse open panicles, short flag leaf blades, and dense fascicles of old persisting sheaths from which the blades tend to disarticulate.
</paragraph>
